  "prompt": "Why can't I answer a question twice on Quora?",
  "response": "On Quora, users are typically not allowed to answer a question more than once to maintain clarity and prevent duplication of content. Here are some reasons for this policy:\n\n1. **Clarity and Readability**: Limiting answers to one per user per question helps keep the information organized, making it easier for users to find relevant responses.\n\n2. **Quality Control**: This approach encourages users to provide their best, most thoughtful answer rather than multiple potentially lesser-quality responses.\n\n3. **Community Standards**: It helps uphold a standard of quality and engagement, fostering a more constructive and respectful environment.\n\nIf you feel like you have more to add or modify in your original answer, you can often edit your response or add additional comments instead.",
